# Docker-Roboshop

A containerized implementation of the Roboshop microservices application using Docker and Docker Compose. This project demonstrates how to build, secure, and deploy multiple interconnected services in a containerized environment.

## Architecture

The application consists of the following microservices:

- Frontend (Nginx)
- User Service
- Catalogue Service
- Cart Service
- Shipping Service
- Payment Service
- MongoDB
- MySQL
- Redis
- RabbitMQ

## Project Structure

```text
Docker-Roboshop/
├── frontend/
├── user/
├── catalogue/
├── cart/
├── shipping/
├── payment/
├── mongodb/
├── mysql/
├── docker-compose.yaml
└── README.md
```

## Features

- Multi-stage Docker builds
- Lightweight production images
- Non-root user implementation
- Docker networking for service communication
- Environment variable configuration
- Docker Compose orchestration
- Container security best practices
- Service isolation and scalability

## Prerequisites

- Docker 20+
- Docker Compose
- Git

## Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Anil-Kumar-Akula/Docker-Roboshop.git
cd Docker-Roboshop
```

## Build Images

Build all services:

```bash
docker compose build
```

Or build an individual service:

```bash
docker build -t frontend ./frontend
docker build -t user ./user
docker build -t catalogue ./catalogue
docker build -t cart ./cart
docker build -t shipping ./shipping
docker build -t payment ./payment
```

## Run the Application

Start all services:

```bash
docker compose up -d
```

Verify running containers:

```bash
docker ps
```

View logs:

```bash
docker compose logs -f
```

Stop all services:

```bash
docker compose down
```

## Docker Best Practices Implemented

### Multi-Stage Builds

Used for Java and Node.js services to reduce final image size and improve security.

### Non-Root User

Containers run with dedicated application users instead of root.

Example:

```dockerfile
RUN addgroup -S roboshop && \
    adduser -S roboshop -G roboshop

USER roboshop
```

### Optimized Images

- Alpine-based images
- Separate build and runtime stages
- Reduced attack surface

## Networking

Docker Compose automatically creates a bridge network allowing services to communicate using service names.

Example:

```text
cart:8080
catalogue:8080
user:8080
shipping:8080
mysql
mongodb
redis
rabbitmq
```

## Environment Variables

Example configuration:

```yaml
environment:
  CART_ENDPOINT: cart:8080
  DB_HOST: mysql
```

## Useful Commands

### List Containers

```bash
docker ps
```

### Inspect Network

```bash
docker network ls
docker network inspect <network-name>
```

### Access a Container

```bash
docker exec -it <container-name> sh
```

### View Logs

```bash
docker logs <container-name>
```

